If it's peer-to-peer network, that means two devices are directly connected to each other without any intermediary nodes then it's fine to exchange data directly through lower layers. Imagine two laptops connected via a cable, direct files transfer is possible with security since the network established there has just two devices.   For network with multiple devices which are connected through various intermediary nodes, security is more important and hence data is directed via physical layer as to avoid attackers from directly accessing your data through application layer.

@sudgamer4639  did you mean to write "then it's fine to exchange data directly WITHOUT going through lower layers" in the peer-to-peer network. Anyway, if that's the case then I totally understand now. Thank you sir

@harmonyOfEureka  peer-to-peer doesn't need servers to transfer data because the nodes to which data is transferred are the end devices (destination devices). Since there are no intermediary nodes like routers, switches direct transfer is possible and quicker as well
